race.description: Party With The Ponies Maiden Plate
race.comment: MISS ELLANEOUS (11) has threatened in much better races and needed the first-up outing in a strong form race at Geelong. She missed a whisker at Ballarat at her only second-up outing, and John Allen is a positive jockey engagement. Maps well, and this is a suitable assignment. BEAU STRADA (7) performed well enough on debut and then improved sharply, beaten a nose at Traralgon, leading from start to finish. Will likely get a dryer surface today, but stays down in the weights and has solid each-way claims. BURLEIGH (1) brings country placings to peak and has scope for more improvement. Was backed off the map at Ararat last time, and Coffey rides from the inside barrier. Has been kept on the fresh side and deserves another chance. Wary of CLEVOR TREVER (3), who debuts for the Paynes. Has been well educated and just missed in a recent Caulfield Heath trial. Egan sticks with that and can use the inside barrier. SWOBODA (14) has a wide gate but went well at Ararat first-up.
